Some areas have experienced flooding after heavy rains hit some parts of Johannesburg on Thursday. The South African Weather Service warned of a slow moving storm currently over Johannesburg with downpours expected to last until late afternoon. Motorists in the area are advised to take extreme caution driving in the flooding especially as the peak time afternoon traffic rush approaches.SA Weather services also reported that severe thunderstorms are observed north-east of Somerset East, moving towards Bedford in the Eastern Cape on Thursday.&nbsp;JHB South: #FLOODING RT @ReenvalSA In Randhart Alberton , courtesy Karin Goosen @TrafficSA pic.twitter.com/5NfQCYKG7D Rob Byrne (@TrafficSA) March 2, 2017-Zingisa Mndayi